# Alfred State College to host 2014 SUNYAC Men’s and Women’s Swimming and Diving Championships

Alfred State College will host the 2014 State University of New York Athletic Conference (SUNYAC) Men’s and Women’s Swimming and Diving Championships from Wednesday, Feb. 19 through Saturday, Feb. 22 at the Alfred State College Aquatic Center.

The event will feature 10 teams from across the SUNY system, including Alfred State, Buffalo State, Cortland, Fredonia, Geneseo, New Paltz, Oneonta, Oswego, Potsdam, and Brockport. The four-day event will feature preliminary races in the morning and finals in the evening.

“We are very excited to be hosting the SUNYAC Swimming and Diving Championships,” said Alfred State College Director of Athletics Daryl Arroyo. “This is a great opportunity to showcase our outstanding facilities and our campus to the SUNYAC community. We are looking forward to a great four days of competition.”

The Alfred State College Aquatic Center is a state-of-the-art facility that features a 50-meter by 25-yard competition pool with two moveable bulkheads, a separate diving well with two 1-meter and two 3-meter boards, and seating for 500 spectators. The facility also includes a 4,000-square-foot strength and conditioning center, a 3,000-square-foot athletic training room, and locker rooms.

The SUNYAC Swimming and Diving Championships will be webcast live on the Alfred State College Athletics website at www.alfredstateathletics.com. For more information on the event, including a complete schedule, visit the SUNYAC website at www.sunyac.com.
